Testing and automation decisions

1. Testing Decisions

Login (Username, Password, Login button)
Forgot Login Info
Register
Navigation menu
Services &amp; News sections
Decision:
Login is business-critical, so it gets maximum testing focus.
Risk-Based Testing
Login → High risk (security + entry point)
Registration → Medium risk
Links/Navigation → Low risk
Decision:
More test scenarios for login (valid, invalid, security, edge cases)
Test Coverage Strategy

Functional Testing
Valid login
Invalid login
Blank fields
Field validations

Negative Testing
Wrong credentials
Labels (Username, Password)
Button visibility

Test Data Decisions
Valid users → for positive testing
Invalid users → for negative testing
Boundary values → long username/password
Decision: Use reusable and maintainable test data

2. Automation Decisions
Login functionality (high priority)
Negative scenarios
Regression scenarios

Framework Design Decision
I use Hybrid Framework (POM + NUnit + Utilities)

Maintainability → Page classes separate UI logic
Reusability → Common methods in BasePage
Scalability → Easy to add new modules

Technical Decisions

Locator Strategy
Prefer: ID / Name
Use XPath only when needed

Wait Strategy

Use Explicit Waits (WebDriverWait)

Avoid Thread.Sleep

Error Handling

Capture error message for invalid login
Take screenshots on failure

3. Security Testing Decisions
